org.phoenixbioinformatics.api.db.api

Class AbstractAccessType

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.poesys.db.dto.AbstractDto
      • org.phoenixbioinformatics.api.db.api.AbstractAccessType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.poesys.db.dto.IDbDto, com.poesys.db.dto.IObserver, com.poesys.db.dto.ISubject, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<com.poesys.db.dto.IDbDto>, IAccessType
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AccessType

    public abstract class AbstractAccessType
extends com.poesys.db.dto.AbstractDto
implements IAccessType

    A data-access layer data-transfer object for the AccessType. This class is an abstract class that contains AndroMDA generated code; change nothing in this class. Instead, override any methods in the concrete subclass generated in the same package. AndroMDA will overwrite this class each time you run it but will never overwrite the concrete subclass.

    A particular kind of access to authorize

    Stereotypes:

    • Persistent
    • SequenceKey

    Class is read/write: true

    Author:
    Poesys/DB Cartridge
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
